#general
Arbitrage: taking advantage of price difference without risk
Hedge: position used to offset potential losses
Insolvency: inability to pay debt
Leverage: multiplies gains and losses, uses borrowed funds
AUM (assets under management): total market value of assets
Valuation: subjective total value of company

#debt
Debt: obligation to repay money with interest
- Default: failure to meet obligations of debt
- Collateral: asset pledged as security for debt
- Guarantor: repays debt in case of default
- Secured debt: backed by collateral (mortgage)
- Unsecured debt: without collateral and guarantor
Credit: potential debt
Bond: public, balloon payment
Loan: private, amortization
- Mortgage: loan secured by real estate
- Payday loan: short-tem, unsecured, high interest rate
Non-performing loan (NPL): loan with late repayments (90d+), unlikely to be repaid in full
Repayment plan: installment schedule of loan

Earnest payment: deposit to seller of high value property (real estate)

#debt
principal: amount loaned
interest: payment from borrower to lender
- Usury: excessive interest rate, illegal
repayment
credit bureau: agency gathering account information from creditors
credit rating agency: company assigning credit ratings
credit rating: evaluation of credit risk of debtor
credit risk: likelihood of debtor defaulting
bankruptcy: process enabling debtor in default to seek relief on part of debt
Synthetic lease: taxed as loan, accounted as lease (off balance sheet), SPE holds asset

#financing
Capital structure: mix of funds used to finance business
- Absolute priority rule: more senior creditors must be paid in full before more junior at bankruptcy
Cost of capital: cost of funds, expected return on capital has to exceed it
Opportunity cost: value of next best alternative
Senior debt: low risk, usually banks, usually secured, highest priority, lowest interest rate
- Covenant: condition borrower needs to fulfull (e.g. LTV ratio, debt coverage ratio)
Junior debt / Subordinated debt: priority below senior, higher risk, higher interest rate
Mezzanine debt: often can be conditionally converted to equity, priority below junior

#investment
Stock based compensation (SBC): equity compensation to employee
Advisory shares: equity compensation to non-employee
Venture debt: loan to fund capital combined with warrants
Venture capital: funds in exchange for ownership stake

