#
Business day convention: date rolling rules
- Date rolling: payment date moved when falling on holiday
- Following:  next business day
- Modified following: next business day, only same calendar month
Day count convention: how interest accrues (30/360, ACT/360, ACT/365)
Interest rate:
- Fixed: constant
- Floating: based on reference rate
- Spread / Margin: added to floating rate
- Default margin: in case of arrears
- Floor: minimum rate
- Cap: maximum rate
Amortization: principal allocation across repayments
- Bullet: all principal on maturity
- Balloon: equal principal except on maturity
- Linear: equal principal
- Annuity: equal payment (principal+interest), initially more interest less principal
Bitemporal modeling: allows handling retroactive changes
- Value date: effective date
- Posting date: technical date
Allocation: repayment distribution
- Waterfall: fee -> interest -> principal
Allocation method:
- Pro rata: proportionally
Accrual: interest calculation
EOD batch: arrears -> accrual -> financial entries
Reversal: opposite financial entry
GL account: aggregate financial bucket
- Posting rules: assign transactions to GL accounts
Impairment: downward revaluation of asset
- Provision: amount set aside to cover expected loss
Arrears: overdue repayment (behind schedule)
- DPD (Days past due): actual date - scheduled date
- Grace period: penalties only start afterwards (may be retroactive)
Capitalization: transfer of accrued interest to principal
- PIK (Payment in kind): pay interest using more debt
